begin_memory_text: My chat partner had some technical issues at the beginning of the session, so it took us about five minutes to get set up. Our initial conversation included introducing ourselves and talking about what was going on with Covid in our cities.
middle_memory_text: We talked more about our personal stories, I told him about my work and hobbies and he told me about his work. We discussed the lockdown measures with Covid in Chicago versus Florida as well as the challenges with mandates versus no mandates.
end_memory_text: My chat partner talked more about his work as an ER doctor and the challenges of treating patients with Covid and now the upcoming influenza season.
rest_of_day_open: My week is going to be very busy with work projects and an event at our community garden. So, I see it being a very good and productive week. I hope to find time to take good care of myself, especially with regard to yoga and eating healthy. I feel more able to focus and that feels good.
critical_positive: I feel my chat partner and I were respectful toward one another. I feel we were both genuinely interested in learning about each others' situations. I felt open and able to share what is going on in my city and life. I felt my chat partner did as well, but I felt I talked more.
critical_negative: As I mentioned in my last post, I feel maybe I talked a bit too much. I wish I would have asked him more questions. I sometimes get enthusiastic about sharing details about things in my life and take too long to describe them! I hope my partner did not find that annoying.
